title: Online search query market share worldwide 2017 , by search engine
summary: This grouped bar chart shows Market Share on the Y-axis for 11 different Responses for 6 groups Google, Yahoo, Bing, AOL, Ask, and Other that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 6 groups, Bing had the highest Market Share in Response Five words and AOL had the lowest Market Share in Response Ten or more words.
Among all the Responses, Ask had the highest Market Share 1937.0 in Response Ten or more words and lowest value 34.0 in Response Total.
There is a gap of 1903.0 between the highest and lowest Market Share found for Ask in Response Ten or more words and Total.
min_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 11 different Responses on X-axis for 6 groups Google, Yahoo, Bing, AOL, Ask, and Other. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Market Share.
Response Five words had the maximum Market Share among all 6 groups, and it was for Bing. The minimum Market Share was observed in Response Ten or more words for AOL.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 11 different Responses on X-axis for 6 groups Google, Yahoo, Bing, AOL, Ask, and Other. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Market Share.
Out of all 6 groups, Bing had the highest Market Share in Response Five words and AOL had the lowest Market Share in Response Ten or more words.
Among all the Responses, Ask had the highest Market Share 1937.0 in Response Ten or more words and lowest value 34.0 in Response Total.
The maximum Market Share for Ask that was found in Response Ten or more words was 56.97 times larger than the minimum Market Share observed in Response Total.
Out of all 6 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum Market Share was found in case of Bing.
Bing had the maximum Market Share out of all 6 groups in Response Five words followed by Bing in Five words, and the minimum Market Share is found for AOL in Ten or more words.
On average, the Response Total had the highest Market Share for all 6 groups Google, Yahoo, Bing, AOL, Ask, and Other. Whereas Three words had the lowest average Market Share.
